The paper deals with a multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) interference channel (IC) and focuses on the channel state information obtained by the transmitters (CSIT) being completely outdated. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with interference alignment (IA) schemes, which are commonly studied in the Signal Processing (cs.SP) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also proposes two schemes that generalize and integrate key features of previous works, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
